<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">For more on the science, track the reporting of <a href="//mashable.com/2015/04/02/california-drought-preview-global-warming-megadrought/">Andrew Freedman</a>, <a href="//blogs.discovermagazine.com/imageo/2015/04/03/north-of-drought-plagued-california-snowpack-in-the-cascades-is-at-record-lows-too/#.VSFJLZTF8do">Tom Yulsman</a> and <a href="//www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/capital-weather-gang/wp/2015/04/02/hot-hands-fingerprints-of-climate-change-all-over-california-drought/">Jason Samenow</a> (among others).</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Given that music fits into my description of multimedia communication, here&#8217;s a suitable soundtrack for California&#8217;s efforts in months and years to come: &#8220;Dry Spell Blues,&#8221; written by Son House during <a href="//uncensoredhistoryoftheblues.purplebeech.com/2011/09/show-54-1930-drought.html">a scorching drought in the South</a>, performed by my former band Uncle Wade.</p>
